locality: N.C. Vallée de la Ouenghi (Rive Droite). Maquis haut. Terrian rocheux. Serpentineux.

Mining area just northwest and adjacent to the Thio. Following primary mine access road north of river. Maquis damaged from roads and mining, with abundant braken fern. Ultramafic substrates, serpentine and pterodites.
N.C. Tontouta River valley on old mining road 14 km from Rt 1, 6 km up road.
Dome du Tiebachi. Moist, dense maquis with small trees and shrub on upper slopes of the mountain.
Vallée de la Tontouta. Maquis arbustif. Sol brun hypermagnésien érodé.
Dumbéa barrage, ca 10.5 km from Rt 1.
